${q_\text{b}}=2$, ${\lambda_\text{r}}=1.33{\lambda_\text{b}}$, chosen by eye to provide the best fit. Theoretical units were converted to physical units using ${\lambda_\text{b}}=0.65\mu m$, $K=125 k_BT$.  \label{fig:Chirality-boundary-conditions-1}}
